==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theropoda
<hw>The*rop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>qh`r</grk> a beast + <?/, <?/, foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An order of carnivorous dinosaurs in which the
feet are less birdlike, and hence more like those of an ordinary
quadruped, than in the Ornithopoda. It includes the rapacious genera
<gen>Megalosaurus</gen>, <gen>Creosaurus</gen>, and their
allies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

